"{\"uid\": \"newsshopper.co.uk-news-national-uk-today-24480177.official-olympic-games-mascots-phryges\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"2024 Paris Olympic GamesSport  The Paris Olympics are underway and like anyGames, there is an official mascot you might spot throughout the competition.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 152, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic and Paralympic mascots are shaped like a traditional French hat.\", \"from\": 154, \"to\": 230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 219, \"end\": 225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999749544784714, \"rank\": 2.5039142040258487e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are\\u00a0mostly red in colour and represent the host nation with blue, white and red\\u00a0stripes, the colours of the France flag.\", \"from\": 232, \"to\": 357, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 345, \"end\": 351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999365206824, \"rank\": 5.535538013889102e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Phryges are the mascots for Paris 2024 but what are they and what do they mean?\", \"from\": 359, \"to\": 438, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 387, \"end\": 397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999836443295, \"rank\": 1.635565178153284e-08, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mesdames et messieurs, la C\\u00e9r\\u00e9monie d'ouverture de#Paris2024Ladies and gentlemen, the Paris 2024 Opening Ceremony.\\ud83d\\udcf8 Getty / Lionel Bonaventurepic.twitter.com/God7bQHvNd  Now that the Olympics have begun, the mascots will be popping up as you tune in to watch the sporting action.\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 719, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 463, \"end\": 475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_C\\u00e9r\\u00e9monie\", \"score\": 0.9999999198400961, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"la C\\u00e9r\\u00e9monie\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_C\\u00e9r\\u00e9monie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_C\\u00e9r\\u00e9monie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"BBC viewers will have spotted some stuffed toys of the mascots sitting on the sofa in the studio.\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 818, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 722, \"end\": 725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9897904765813814, \"rank\": 0.008818470448636876, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meet the#Paris2024mascots, the Phryges!\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 859, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\ud83c\\uddeb\\ud83c\\uddf7\\u2728https://t.co/67BKrVSo0i  TheOlympics websiteexplains the idea behind the mascots, saying: \\\"The Paris 2024 mascots are called the Phryges, based on the traditional Phrygian hats that serve as a symbol for freedom.\\\"\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 1076, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 874, \"end\": 878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"t.co\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}, {\"begin\": 995, \"end\": 1002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygians\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Phryges\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygians\"}, {\"begin\": 1029, \"end\": 1037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.929780927588027e-17, \"text\": \"Phrygian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It added: \\\"These hats are seen everywhere in French culture and everyday life, from paintings to stamps, town halls to coins, the French Republic to the modern day.\", \"from\": 1078, \"to\": 1242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1126, \"end\": 1140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1218, \"end\": 1226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic\", \"score\": 0.9999261231222146, \"rank\": 7.264492106383271e-05, \"text\": \"Republic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They are a symbol of French history and values, the perfect representation for their home Games.\\\"\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1342, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1269, \"end\": 1283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Recommended reading:  The website further explains: \\\"The\\u00a0Olympic Phryge\\u00a0is in the shape of one of the traditional Phrygian caps, bright red with a French tricolour trim of blue, white and red.\", \"from\": 1346, \"to\": 1538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1463, \"end\": 1471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.929780927588027e-17, \"text\": \"Phrygian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\"}, {\"begin\": 1496, \"end\": 1512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French tricolour\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The\\u00a0Paralympic Phryge\\u00a0takes the same form but with a jumping blade, like the one used by Paralympic athletes.\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1648, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Phrygian cap has been a powerful symbol throughout history, representing the French fight for freedom through revolution, the establishment of Bastille Day as their national day on 14 July, and of course, the core French values:\\u00a0Libert\\u00e9, Egalit\\u00e9, Fraternit\\u00e9\\u00a0(Liberty, Equality, Fraternity).\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1658, \"end\": 1670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Phrygian cap\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\"}, {\"begin\": 1735, \"end\": 1741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999749544784714, \"rank\": 2.5039142040258487e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Now, in 2024, the Phryges take on new symbolism for the Olympic Games and Paralympic Games in Paris.\\\"\", \"from\": 1947, \"to\": 2049, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2045, \"end\": 2050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1424033758707636e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia